# Copy this to .env for local development.
# On Railway, set these in the service's Variables dashboard — never commit real values.

# ── Required ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
LICHESS_TOKEN=your_lichess_api_token_here

# ── Learning storage: pick ONE backend ────────────────────────────────────────
# Both store the same things: best.pt, latest.pt, ouroboros.db (~500 MB total).
# The replay buffer is NOT synced — it regenerates from self-play quickly.

# Option A — Google Drive (15 GB free, more than enough)
# Setup steps:
#   1. Go to console.cloud.google.com → create a project
#   2. Enable "Google Drive API"
#   3. IAM & Admin → Service Accounts → Create service account → skip roles
#   4. Click the service account → Keys → Add Key → JSON → download the file
#   5. Share your Drive folder with the service account email (Editor role)
#   6. Paste the folder's ID from its URL: drive.google.com/drive/folders/THIS_PART
#   7. Base64-encode the JSON key:  base64 -w0 key.json   (Linux/Mac)
#                                   certutil -encode key.json tmp && findstr /v CERT tmp  (Windows)
# GDRIVE_KEY=eyJ0eXBlIjoic2VydmljZV9hY2NvdW50IiwicH...   (base64 of the JSON key file)
# GDRIVE_FOLDER_ID=1BxiMVs0XRA5nFMdKvBdBZjgmUUqptlbs

# Option B — Hugging Face Hub (50 GB free private repo, simpler setup)
# Setup steps:
#   1. Sign up at huggingface.co
#   2. Create a new PRIVATE repo at huggingface.co/new
#   3. Get a write token at huggingface.co/settings/tokens
# HF_TOKEN=hf_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# HF_REPO=your-hf-username/your-repo-name

# ── Optional overrides ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HARDWARE_PROFILE=small          # small | medium | large
# MODE=auto                       # auto | play | train
# MATCHMAKER_ENABLED=true
# SEED_GAMES=5000                 # reduce for faster first boot on cloud
# SEED_TRAIN_STEPS=1000
# ACCEPT_RATED=true
# ACCEPT_CASUAL=true
# MAX_CONCURRENT_GAMES=1
# CHAT_ENABLED=true
# WINNER_IMITATION=true
